Package hackerrank

Class TempleRun

  • java.lang.Object
    • hackerrank.TempleRun
  • public class TempleRun
extends java.lang.Object
    You are a ninja in a strange environment modeled as an undirected, unweighted, connected graph with n ≥ 5 nodes. Nodes are identified with an integer between 0 and n - 1. In this graph, there are 5 special nodes; s, the ninja's original location, e, the location of an alien base, and t1, t2, t3 are the locations of 3 sacred temples. You are given n, the number of nodes, the list of edges in the graph (each edge is a pair of different numbers between 0 and n-1), and the 5 special nodes: s, e, t1, t2 and t3. All those node IDs are distinct numbers between 0 and n-1. At time 0, we are at node s. At the same time, 3 alients leave from the alien base. Each alien goes towards one of the temples, each following the shortest path to that temple. Both you and the aliens can move one edge per time step. Return true if you can reach all 3 sacred temples (in any order) before the enemies get to ANY of the temples. That is, you need to find if the ninja can follow a path such that there is a time step where the ninja has allready been to t1, t2 and t3, but no alien has reached any one of t1, t2, or t3. If the ninja reaches the last temple at the same time that the alients reach the temple, we should return false. See if this URL is live for some explanatory shapes.
